You may have noticed that one of our popular databases, the Texas Prison Inmates database, has been taken down. The database contains public information on more than 140,000 inmates in state custody, and the decision to remove it, even temporarily, was not one we made lightly. We want to explain why.

We first posted the prison database in 2010. All of the data in it comes directly from the Texas Department of Criminal Justice,
